descript.abstract: U.S. Cities represents locations for cities within United States with populations of 10,000 or greater and all state capitals.
descript.purpose: This dataset is used to create the US Map Templates series.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:100,000.

citeinfo.title: Summary Tape File-1C (STF-1C)
citeinfo.othercit: The Summary Tape File-1C (STF-1C) data is based on the 1990 Census of Population. The geospatial data is calculated from the latitude/longitude coordinate attributes.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Created a data set by extracting places of 10,000 or more inhabitants from U.S. Bureau of the Census 1990 Summary Tape File 1C (STF-1C). Ran ArcView command Add Event Theme on the data set to create the point location centroids shapefile. Converted to North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83) by splitting the United States into Alaska, Hawaii, and the 48 contiguous states (including District of Columbia); converting each to NAD83; then merging them together. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was calculated from latitude/longitude coordinates from the U.S. Bureau of the Census 1990 Summary Tape File 1C (STF-1C). The horizontal positional accuracy is unknown.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is exported using Avenue request ExportClean. This request verifies and enforces the correctness of shapes.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
